                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom (
                        Winant
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d665</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">665</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="665" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/4–146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-09T18:00:00-05:00">April 9, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3060. For Hawkins. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 3635, Apr l.<note n="59" xml:id="d665fn59">Not printed.</note> Please inform Brit that they
                    can make no statement on our authority at this time regarding approx date
                    preliminary trade meeting, that we will give them a definite answer by Apr 16 or
                    17 and that decision will probably be to postpone negotiating meeting until
                    early 1947.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
